The murder case against 40-year-old Soweto born rapper Thulani Ngcobo popularly known as Pitch Black Afro is expected to continue on Thursday in the Johannesburg Magistrate’s Court. Ngcobo has been charged with murder and defeating the ends of justice. This after being suspected of having killed his wife Catherine Modusane on the 31st of December at a Bed and Breakfast in Yeoville, Johannesburg. It’s understood that Modusane had died of natural causes, however a few days later a murder docket was opened after foul play was suspected. Neighbours reported hearing the couple arguing the night before. Modusane allegedly sustained injuries to her upper body.  